  "text": "The demographic characteristics of the three patient groups (SS-SSc, pSS and SSc) are summarized in Table 2 . Women represented 90% of the patients in each group. The mean age at the diagnosis of SS or SSc was similar to the several groups of [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] patients (range 50-55 yrs). The mean durations of symptoms were 7.4, 8.4 and 12.8 yrs for SS-SSc, SSc and pSS groups, respectively. The duration of SS symptoms was significantly higher in the pSS group than in the SS-SSc group (P ¼ 0.0004). SS and SSc characteristics of the patients in the 3 groups are indicated in Table 3 .",
